Erdogan’s Party Has 44 Percent Public Support, Aksam Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-03-10T06:53:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/erdogan-s-party-has-44-percent-public-support-aksam-says.html
Prime Minister Recep Tayyip
Erdogan’s governing party has the backing of 44 percent of
voters ahead of June’s parliamentary election, Aksam newspaper
reported citing a poll by research company Iksara.  The main opposition  Republican People’s Party  has 24
percent support and the Nationalist Action Party 14 percent,
Istanbul-based Aksam said citing the poll of 4,000 people in  Turkey ’s 81 provinces between Feb. 15 and Feb. 21.  The survey didn’t distribute the votes of undecided voters,
which were 10 percent of total, according to Aksam. No margin of
error was given.  More than half of voters opposed Erdogan’s approach towards
protests concerning curbs on alcohol, Aksam said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
